From 158fe8bd59f8d6ae0c04a8baf2f16e64e7376999 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ASK2 build <ask2@vyos-ls1046a>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 04:52:48 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman: PCD CC/KG body-4 -- add_key, modify_next_action,
 kg_attach_cc

Replaces the three -EOPNOTSUPP stubs left in place by PR14c-prep / PR14b-body
with their real bodies, completing the silicon programming path from a KG
scheme through a CC tree's group table down to per-key action descriptors.

Changes:
- fman_keygen.c: add internal helper keygen_scheme_set_ccbs() that does an
  AR-mediated indirect read-modify-write of a single scheme's KGSE_CCBS
  register, preserving every other KGSE_* field that keygen_scheme_setup()
  programmed.  Exported via fman_keygen_internal.h.
- fman_pcd_internal.h: add cross-TU accessor fman_pcd_cc_tree_group_table_off()
  so fman_pcd_kg.c can read the private tree handle's group-table MURAM offset
  without exposing struct fman_pcd_cc_tree's layout.
- fman_pcd_cc.c: implement fman_pcd_cc_node_add_key() and
  fman_pcd_cc_node_modify_next_action() under node->lock (spin_lock_bh,
  softirq-safe).  add_key encodes the AD slot first via cc_encode_ad
  (PR14c-body-3) before writing key+mask bytes, so a partially-populated
  row cannot misroute -- the AD stays in its all-zero FQ-0-trap state on
  encoder failure.  modify_next_action only mutates the AD; key bytes are
  immutable per the ABI doc.  Also drops the __maybe_unused attr from
  cc_encode_ad now that it has real callers, and adds the cross-TU
  accessor body.
- fman_pcd_kg.c: implement fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc() that resolves the tree's
  group-table offset, masks to the low 24 MURAM-addressable bits, and calls
  keygen_scheme_set_ccbs() under pcd->lock to update only KGSE_CCBS.

Verification on Cobalt 100 ARM64 (make Image modules, kernel 6.18.28):
  ffff8000809beb68 T keygen_scheme_set_ccbs
  ffff8000809bff28 T fman_pcd_kg_attach_cc
  ffff8000809c0478 t cc_encode_ad         (no longer DCE'd)
  ffff8000809c0550 T fman_pcd_cc_node_modify_next_action
  ffff8000809c0618 T fman_pcd_cc_node_add_key
  ffff8000809c0db8 T fman_pcd_cc_tree_group_table_off
  + __ksymtab entries for all four public ABI exports.

Locking summary:
- node->lock (spinlock_t): protects per-node match-table/AD-table writes
  against softirq-context flow-table updates from PR15+.
- pcd->lock (mutex): held across keygen_scheme_set_ccbs to serialise the
  AR-indirect-window read-modify-write against any other scheme writer.

ABI: no change to <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>; this body lights up entry points
whose contracts the header already documents.

Refs: ASK2 spec v1.1, RM 8.7.4 (KGSE_CCBS), 8.7.4.2 (CC match table),
      8.7.4.3 Table 8-119 (AD record), PR14c-body-3 (commit 7ebbb4e8c).
